            "is_input_type": true,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "A and B start moving simultaneously towards each other from points X and Y respectively. A starts at the speed of 2 m/sec in the first second and then increases his speed every second by 3 m/sec . Similarly, B starts at 3 m/sec and increases his speed every second by some integral speed in m/sec . They meet at the end of nth second (n > 2) and speed of B during nth second was decuple of that of A. Find the distance (in meters) between points X and Y. [decuple = ten folds]<ul class='list-group'><li class='list-group-item'><B><a href='#quesSol1575854' data-toggle='collapse' aria-expanded='true'> Answer key/Solution</a></B></li></ul>",
            "options": [],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "5292"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct Answer : <b>5292</B><div ><img src=https://clsite-file.s3.amazonaws.com/LSTQuestionImg/773316/770583/97s.gif></div></div>"
